4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,500
Now, and the relationship between

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:19,000
them, symmetry is between them.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
So actually before we talk about supersymmetry,

7
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
we should talk again about fermions and bosons.

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,000
I want to tell you some

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,000
odd and peculiar facts about fermions first.

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,500
No, before we even talk about

11
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:38,000
fermions, let's talk about rotations in space.

12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:43,500
Now, we always say that a rotation by 2 pi

13
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:49,000
is equivalent to no rotation at all, but it's not true.

14
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,500
It's not true. Let me assure you

15
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,000
that if I take my hand like this,

16
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,000
and I rotate it like this,

17
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,500
and I rotate my wrist by 2

18
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:02,000
pi, it is not like doing nothing.

19
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:06,000
But then I tell you if I rotate it by

20
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,000
4 pi, which I will do for you in a minute,

21
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,500
if I rotate it by 4

22
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:13,000
pi, it's equivalent to doing nothing.

23
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
So you want to see me

24
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,000
rotate by 4 pi, don't you?

25
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
You're going to say, I can't

26
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
do it. Oh, yes, I can.

27
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,500
We started this way, palm up, rotate

28
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:24,000
by 2 pi, it starts to hurt.

29
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Palm up, and I come back to nothing.

30
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:33,000
This is a topological theorem about rotations in space.

31
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
It's a topological theorem, and let me tell

32
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:39,000
you, let me explain the topological theorem to you.

33
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,500
I've proved it. I've proved it.

34
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:44,000
I don't need to prove it mathematically.

35
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:48,000
I've proved it by hand waving.

36
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:53,000
I've proved it by hand waving. Exactly right.

37
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:01,000
But let me tell you what the theorem actually says.

38
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Here's the theorem. Take a box.

39
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,000
The box has walls. In that box,

40
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,000
put a basketball or some sort of object,

41
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,500
and connect that basketball to the walls by

42
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:18,000
strings, any number of strings, it doesn't matter.

43
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,500
Just connect them by strings. Connect

44
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:23,000
it to the front wall, back wall.

45
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,500
Now, I tell you, and I think you'll believe me, that

46
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:30,000
if I take this ball and rotate it by 2 pi,

47
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,500
I'm going to get a hell of a tangle.

48
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:35,000
The strings are going to get all tangled up.

49
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,000
And the question is, can I untangle

50
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
them by looping them over the ball,

51
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
by without rotating the ball further,

52
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
rotate it around by 2 pi,

53
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,500
can I get rid of the tangle

54
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:50,000
and bring it back to this configuration?

55
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,000
Anybody know the answer?

56
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Rotated by 2 pi.

57
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,000
No, no, no, you're not allowed to rotate the box.

58
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:01,000
The box is fixed.

59
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
So this is a theorem about

60
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,000
rotations of the ball keeping spatial infinity,

61
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,500
the box really represents spatial

62
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:12,000
infinity, keeping the spatial infinity fixed.

63
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,000
You're not allowed to rotate the box.

64
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
So, question. Can I or

65
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
can I not undo that rotation?

66
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Rotate by another 2 pi.

67
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Not yet.

68
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Suppose we do not.

69
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,500
We simply rotate by 2 pi and we ask,

70
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:30,000
can we undo it by moving around the strings,

71
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,000
taking them over the ball,

72
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,000
doing whatever we have to do.

73
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,500
The strings are flexible, they're

74
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:39,000
even stretchable, but they're unbreakable.

75
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:43,000
And they're connected both to the ball and the boundary.

76
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Mathematically, it's the same operation

77
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
as trying to undo this.

78
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,000
The theorem is,

79
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
it says that a rotation by

80
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
4 pi, that you can undo it.

81
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,500
So, the answer is for any rotation

82
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:04,000
by an even number of 2 pi's,

83
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
you can undo it by moving the strings around and,

84
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,000
you know, taking them over the ball and so forth.

85
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:14,000
And it's a topological theorem about the equivalence between

86
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:18,000
a rotation by 2 pi and no rotation at all.

87
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,000
They're not equivalent, really.

88
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,000
A rotation by 2 pi is

89
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,000
not equivalent topologically to no rotation,

90
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,000
but a rotation by 4 pi is.

91
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:31,000
This is kind of unintuitive, but it's true.

92
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Okay.

93
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Let's now come to the

94
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:41,000
properties of wave functions of particles.

95
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:44,000
And now I'm thinking simply about their spin.

96
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Imagine nailing down the position of the particle,

97
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,000
and the only thing that's important now is,

98
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:54,000
the spin of the particle.

99
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,500
And the spin of a particle

100
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,000
is described by a quantum state.

101
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Let's call it S for spin.

102
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,000
I'm either thinking about fermions or bosons.

103
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:08,000
In the case of fermions, the spin is half integer.

104
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,000
In the case of bosons, it's integer.

105
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,500
Now the question is, what happens

106
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:16,000
to the state of a particle

107
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,000
if you rotate the particle by 2 pi?

108
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Now you can imagine for an

109
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,000
electron actually doing this in the laboratory,

110
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,500
how would you actually rotate the

111
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:26,000
spin of an electron by 2 pi?

112
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Anybody know a good way to rotate the...

113
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,000
You can grab it with your hand and rotate it,

114
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,000
but that doesn't work so well.

115
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Magnetic field.

116
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,000
You put it in a strong...

117
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Two ways you could do it.

118
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,000
You can put it into a strong magnetic field,

119
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,500
and then rotate the magnetic

120
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:46,000
field around until it comes back.

121
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,000
You can actually do something else.

122
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:51,000
If the spin happens to lie in the vertical direction,

123
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,500
you can put a magnetic field in and

124
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:54,000
just have it process by itself around there.

125
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
You don't have to rotate the magnetic field.

126
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Either way will do.

127
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:03,000
You can rotate the spin of a charged particle

128
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,500
simply by grabbing it with

129
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:08,000
a magnetic field and rotating it.

130
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:13,000
What happens to the state of a spin particle

131
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,000
when you do rotate it by 2 pi?

132
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Well, usually we say it has to be

133
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,000
it has to come back to itself.

134
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:23,000
After all, rotation by 2 pi is nothing at all.

135
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:30,000
But we found out that rotation by 2 pi

136
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:33,000
does... can do something.

137
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,000
So we might suspect then

138
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,500
that if we rotate the spin

139
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:38,000
of a particle by 2 pi,

140
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,000
it gets... something happens to it.

141
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,000
The simplest thing that could happen to it

142
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:45,000
is it could just get multiplied by a number.

143
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,000
So if I multiply by a number

144
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,000
instead of some other more complicated operator,

145
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,000
well, that's a little complicated.

146
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Why? Because we really, we secretly believe

147
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:02,000
that no experiment will detect the rotation by 2 pi.

148
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,000
And if we multiply the wave function of a particle,

149
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:08,000
for example, by a phase or by a minus 1,

150
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,000
that won't change any physics.

151
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,000
We really secretly believe nothing experimental

152
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,000
will be detected by rotating by 2 pi.

153
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,000
One possibility is it gets multiplied by 1.

154
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Another possibility is it gets multiplied by a phase.

155
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
But here's what we do know.

156
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
If we rotate by 4 pi,

157
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,000
if we rotate by 2 pi,

158
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:32,000
and that gives us some sort of phase,

159
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,000
at e to the i theta,

160
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,000
then rotating again by 2 pi,

161
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:39,000
we'll just square this.

162
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,000
And now we know that rotating by 4 pi

163
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:45,000
is equivalent to doing nothing at all.

164
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,000
Okay?

165
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,000
So if we rotate by 4 pi,

166
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,000
we'll just square this.

167
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,000
And now we know that rotating by 4 pi

168
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
is equivalent to doing nothing at all.

169
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,000
And now we know that rotating by 4 pi

170
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,000
is equivalent to doing nothing at all.

171
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,000
So we can say that the mathematical argument

172
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
says that xi squared must equal 1,

173
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,000
and there's only two possibilities,

174
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
xi is equal to plus 1 or minus 1.

175
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,000
So we could have either possibility

176
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:12,000
when you rotate a particle by 2 pi

177
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,000
just at spin,

178
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,000
you either multiply it by plus 1,

179
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,000
or you multiply it by 2 pi.

180
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,000
And that's the answer.

181
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:21,000
An interesting question is,

182
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,000
can you ever imagine,

183
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,000
just as a side issue,

184
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:29,000
is there ever any experimental

185
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:33,000
observable consequence

186
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
of the fact,

187
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,000
the potential fact,

188
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,000
that the wave function of a particle

189
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,000
might change sign

190
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,000
when you rotate the particle.

191
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,000
And it was generally confirmed

192
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,000
that the magnetic field

193
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,000
was considered to be a totally

194
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,000
unphysical operation,

195
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:53,000
you could never detect it.

196
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,000
In other words,

197
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,000
here would be the experiment.

198
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
You take a whole family of electrons

199
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,000
all prepared identically.

200
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,000
You take half of them

201
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,000
and you stick them into a magnetic field,

202
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,000
and you rotate the magnetic field by 2 pi.

203
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,000
You take the other half

204
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,000
and you do nothing with them.

205
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:13,000
At the end of the day,

206
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,000
is there any experimental difference between them?

207
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,000
No, you cannot tell the difference

208
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,000
which ones got rotated.

209
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,000
But you can do something else,

210
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,000
and I'll tell you what it is.

211
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,000
You can do a two-slit experiment.

212
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Just to tell you the meaning

213
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,000
of this odd mathematical fact,

214
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,000
you can do a two-slit experiment

215
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,000
in which you take electrons,

216
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,000
let's start with a single electron,

217
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,000
not multiple electrons,

218
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,000
or one by one.

219
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,000
We take electrons one by one

220
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,000
and we send them through.

221
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,000
It either goes through the upper slit

222
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,000
or the lower slit.

223
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,000
We don't know which.

224
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,000
We're not allowed to look,

225
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,000
because if we look,

226
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,000
we will destroy the interference pattern over here.

227
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,000
Some interference pattern over here.

228
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:01,000
But now what we're going to do,

229
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,000
without looking at whether the electron is here or here,

230
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:05,000
we're going to place a magnetic field over here,

231
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,000
a B field over here.

232
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,000
We'll also do the same thing over here.

233
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,000
And we'll imagine

234
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,000
that the electron is here,

235
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,000
and the electron gets temporarily trapped

236
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,000
in this region by whatever.

237
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,000
Temporarily trapped

238
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,000
and then re-emitted.

239
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,000
If we do absolutely nothing

240
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,000
to these B fields,

241
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,000
we'll still get some interference pattern here.

242
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,000
Either the electron goes up through here

243
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,000
and gets stuck in the B field

244
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
and then gets re-emitted,

245
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,000
B field is not very interesting,

246
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,000
or same thing over here.

247
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,000
But now we do the following.

248
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,000
We do the two-slit experiment

249
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,000
and while the electron

250
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,000
is trapped in one of these two,

251
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,000
we rotate one of them and not the other.

252
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,000
We rotate one of them

253
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,000
and not the other.

254
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,000
Then the wave function here

255
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:57,000
may or may not get multiplied

256
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,000
by a minus sign,

257
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,000
but let's suppose it does.

258
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,000
The wave function in here does not get multiplied

259
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,000
by a minus sign.

260
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,000
It either gets multiplied

261
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,000
by a minus sign or a plus sign.

262
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,000
If it gets multiplied by a plus sign,

263
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,000
no detection.

264
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:17,000
If it gets multiplied by a minus sign,

265
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,000
and this one, the wave function coming out of here

266
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,000
does not get, what does

267
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,000
that do to the interference pattern?

268
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
It shifts it.

269
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,000
It shifts it up half a wavelength.

270
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,000
It shifts maxima to minima.

271
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,000
It shifts maxima to minima.

272
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,000
So yes, you can detect

273
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,000
this odd sign change,

274
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,000
but only by splitting a beam of electrons

275
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,000
but only by splitting a beam of electrons

276
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,000
and then rotating half the beam

