00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,000
and not the other half beam.

278
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,000
So it is an experimental,

279
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,000
it's a very interesting experiment.

280
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,000
It's a real phenomenon.

281
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,000
But if you were to take the whole experiment

282
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,000
and rotate all of it,

283
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,000
both magnetic fields simultaneously,

284
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,000
then you detect nothing.

285
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,000
Okay?

286
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,000
Alright.

287
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,000
It's very similar in mathematical structure

288
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,000
to the story

289
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:05,000
that if you rotate the ball

290
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,000
without rotating the box,

291
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,000
without rotating the box,

292
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:11,000
you can detect the fact

293
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,000
that you've rotated it by 2 pi.

294
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,000
If you're allowed to rotate

295
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,000
the whole thing,

296
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,000
ball and box, of course you can't.

297
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,000
So it's a similar kind of thing.

298
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:23,000
If you rotate it by 4 pi...

299
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,000
Yeah, exactly.

300
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,000
If you rotate the magnetic field

301
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,000
by 4 pi,

302
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,000
the effect goes away.

303
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,000
Right.

304
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,000
And this incident has been done

305
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,000
in the laboratory.

306
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,000
It was an experiment that was suggested

307
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,000
by Aharonov and myself in 1967.

308
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:43,000
It was actually done.

309
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,000
That's what you said.

310
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,000
Yeah, okay, so for...

311
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,000
Okay, so now you could...

312
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,000
You could do experiments with electrons,

313
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,000
you could do experiments with

314
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,000
charged ions of various kinds,

315
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
and you could see which ones

316
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,000
fall into the category

317
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,000
of getting a minus one

318
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,000
and which ones don't.

319
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,000
The ones that don't have a minus one

320
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,000
are the ones where the interference pattern

321
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,000
does not shift.

322
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,000
The ones that do get a minus sign

323
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,000
are the ones where the interference pattern

324
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,000
does shift.

325
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,000
The answer is all fermions

326
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
get the minus sign,

327
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,000
all bosons do not get the minus sign.

328
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,000
That's an...

329
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,000
First of all,

330
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
it would be an experimental fact

331
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,000
if you really did the experiment.

332
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,000
It's also deeply embedded in the structure

333
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
of the mathematics

334
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,000
of quantum field theory

335
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,000
and quantum mechanics.

336
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,000
All right, so that's an interesting distinction

337
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,000
between fermions and bosons.

338
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,000
Yeah?

339
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,000
How does the analogy with the springs work?

340
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,000
Uh...

341
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,000
The analogy with the springs...

342
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Um...

343
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,000
Well,

344
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,000
roughly speaking,

345
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,000
bosons behave as if they weren't

346
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,000
connected by strings to the wall.

347
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,000
Fermions have some memory

348
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,000
of having been rotated by two pi,

349
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,000
so they have a sort of connection

350
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:07,000
to things which remembers

351
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,000
whether they rotated by two pi.

352
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,000
This is just a method

353
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
that's been used

354
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,000
to find out

355
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,000
the mathematical way to see

356
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,000
the topology,

357
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,000
the topological fact that rotation by two pi

358
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,000
is not so innocent

359
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,000
whereas rotation by four pi is.

360
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,000
But once you know that,

361
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,000
I think we forget about this.

362
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Are they in the same quantum state?

363
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Which?

364
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Once that rotated two pi

365
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,000
and one that isn't rotated?

366
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:39,000
Yeah, well, no.

367
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,000
In this experiment,

368
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,000
yeah, the quantum state of this one

369
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,000
is localized over here.

370
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,000
So what's the idea?

371
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:49,000
The idea is you create

372
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,000
one way or another a superposition

373
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,000
of states in which the electron

374
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,000
is here or it's here.

375
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Not two electrons.

376
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,000
An electron which is either over here,

377
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,000
so a wave function which consists of two bulges,

378
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,000
probability a half

379
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,000
of the electron to be over here,

380
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,000
probability a half of the electron

381
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,000
to be over here.

382
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,000
Now, both of these electrons now,

383
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,000
after you've...

384
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,000
Not both of the electrons, one electron

385
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
but if the electron is here,

386
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,000
we're actually putting it inside a box.

387
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,000
Put it inside a box.

388
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,000
So we create an electron over here.

389
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,000
We split the beam,

390
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,000
which means we create a superposition

391
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,000
of states where it might be here

392
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,000
or it might be here

393
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,000
with probability a half.

394
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,000
And then we rotate this box.

395
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,000
Put a magnetic field in it.

396
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,000
We rotate it.

397
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,000
We don't ask whether there's

398
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,000
an electron in it or not.

399
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Whether or not there is an electron in it,

400
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,000
we rotate the box.

401
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,000
Now, to start with,

402
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,000
the wave function was a sum of two terms.

403
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Psi one,

404
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,000
which is the wave function in here,

405
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,000
and psi two,

406
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:57,000
which is the wave function here.

407
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Psi one plus psi two

408
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,000
was the full wave function.

409
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,000
Now we rotate

410
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,000
the right-hand box

411
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,000
without...

412
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,000
If we rotate both boxes for the electron,

413
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,000
electron being a fermion,

414
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,000
then the whole wave function changes sign.

415
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,000
If the whole wave function

416
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,000
changes sign,

417
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,000
remember all physical quantities

418
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,000
are proportional to the wave function

419
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,000
times its own complex conjugate,

420
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:25,000
and the minus sign will cancel out.

421
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:27,000
But now supposing we rotate

422
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:29,000
one box relative to the other.

423
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,000
Then what happens

424
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,000
is after the...

425
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,000
after the rotation,

426
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,000
this wave function has changed sign,

427
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,000
this one has not.

428
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,000
Let me give you a consequence of that.

429
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,000
If these two wave functions

430
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,000
were identical,

431
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,000
about reflection,

432
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,000
about the center here,

433
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,000
that would say that after the rotation,

434
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,000
the wave function must vanish

435
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:55,000
at the center here.

436
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,000
If psi one and psi two

437
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,000
have exactly the same shape,

438
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,000
and let's even suppose...

439
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:03,000
Yeah, alright.

440
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,000
After we bring them back together again.

441
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,000
By symmetry, the wave function will vanish

442
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,000
at the center here

443
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:11,000
if the wave function is odd.

444
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,000
If the wave function is even,

445
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,000
then after we bring them back together again,

446
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,000
it doesn't have to vanish at the center.

447
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,000
So an interesting consequence of this

448
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,000
is if this one is a fermion

449
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,000
and we rotate by two pi

450
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,000
and then bring the wave functions back together again,

451
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,000
we will never find the electron at the center.

452
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,000
That's an example

453
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,000
of an interference phenomena.

454
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,000
But,

455
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,000
the point is that there is a difference

456
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,000
between psi one minus psi two

457
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,000
and psi one plus psi two.

458
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,000
And that difference

459
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,000
can be experimentally detected.

460
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Is it the case that

461
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,000
if you don't do a full rotation,

462
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,000
that basically the amount of rotation

463
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,000
is half as much for a boson

464
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,000
or twice as much

465
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,000
or something like that?

466
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,000
Well,

467
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,000
there is something like that,

468
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,000
but that's not...

469
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,000
Yeah, there is...

470
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
Would you say that you could tell

471
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,000
the loophole with the electron wet proof?

472
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,000
If you look for the electron

473
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,000
in such a way that you can tell afterwards

474
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,000
which one it was in,

475
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,000
then the interference pattern is destroyed.

476
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,000
What happens if instead of a screen

477
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,000
you test...

478
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,000
Let's say you put it all right,

479
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:23,000
all the spins are all in one direction

480
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,000
and at the screen you test

481
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,000
the resulting spin.

482
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,000
Will that destroy the interference pattern?

483
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,000
All the spins are in one direction.

484
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Okay,

485
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,000
they are all in the same direction.

486
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Oh, I see.

487
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,000
They still stay in the same direction,

488
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,000
just get a minus sign.

489
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,000
That's right.

490
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,000
Is it true that if you only

491
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:49,000
if you didn't turn it to pi,

492
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,000
to turn it just pi...

493
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,000
Oh, then it's certainly detectable

494
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,000
to change the direction of the spin.

495
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,000
Then the interference pattern

496
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,000
would be destroyed.

497
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,000
Right, the interference pattern

498
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,000
would be completely destroyed.

499
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,000
Basically, as you tune it,

500
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,000
you can tune it to get an interference pattern.

501
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,000
That's right.

502
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,000
If you rotate that spin,

503
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,000
you tend to destroy...

504
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:15,000
Rotate the spin by anything

505
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:17,000
whether it's 2 pi or 4 pi,

506
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,000
you'll lose some of the interference pattern.

507
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,000
If you actually rotate it by 180 degrees,

508
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:23,000
you completely destroy the interference pattern.

509
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,000
Right, that's correct.

510
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,000
You can't interfere an up spin with a down spin.

511
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,000
You can only interfere things

512
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,000
which are otherwise the same.

513
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,000
Yeah.

514
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,000
Good, all right.

515
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,000
Good, so we now have some bits of information

516
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,000
about fermions.

517
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,000
They change sign on the rotation.

518
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,000
They don't.

519
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:51,000
Now, let's come to yet another question.

520
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,000
Let's come to a question about Feynman diagrams.

521
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,000
The kind of Feynman diagrams

522
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
I have in mind now

