00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,000
the amplitude that you start with nothing

541
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,000
and you get nothing.

542
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,000
So it's part of the value of the function.

543
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,000
So it's part of the vacuum structure.

544
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,000
The diagram has a value.

545
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
That value is a contribution

546
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,000
to the vacuum energy.

547
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,000
Let's not try to understand

548
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,000
precisely why that's so.

549
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,000
But just like the diagram

550
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,000
which is attached to the particle here

551
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,000
shifts the energy of the particle,

552
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,000
a diagram like this

553
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,000
in free-floating space

554
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,000
would shift the energy of a vacuum.

555
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,000
The question is,

556
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,000
how do you know

557
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:13,000
how much energy is in the vacuum?

558
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,000
The question is,

559
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,000
does it shift it up or down?

560
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,000
And we're going to find out

561
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,000
that the answer is different

562
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,000
for bosons and fermions.

563
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,000
So, let's think about

564
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,000
the sign,

565
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,000
just the sign

566
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,000
of a diagram which looks like this

567
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,000
for fermions or bosons.

