00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,000
without doing any work at all,

570
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,000
we can prove

571
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,000
the desired result,

572
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,000
which I will show you now.

573
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,000
No work at all.

574
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,000
Very little.

575
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,000
Very little.

576
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,000
Here's the way we do it.

577
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,000
Let's start

578
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,000
with the boson case.

579
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,000
Well, let's start,

580
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:03,000
we can take both cases simultaneously.

581
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,000
And let's begin

582
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,000
with two loops.

583
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,000
In other words,

584
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,000
there are, what is a loop?

585
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,000
A loop is a pair of particles

586
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,000
in the subsequent annihilation of it.

587
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,000
Or you can just think of it

588
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,000
as a particle going around

589
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,000
in a closed loop in space-time.

590
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,000
You can either think of it

591
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,000
as a particle going around

592
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,000
in a closed loop in space-time,

593
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,000
or more physically,

594
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:31,000
less colorfully,

595
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,000
it's a production of a pair of particles,

596
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,000
a particle-antiparticle pair,

597
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,000
and then the annihilation.

598
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,000
Okay, here there are

599
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,000
two loops.

600
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:43,000
One loop is a positive sign

601
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,000
of the diagram associated

602
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,000
with just one loop.

603
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:49,000
It can either be positive or negative.

604
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,000
What about

605
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,000
two separate loops like this?

606
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,000
The Feynman diagram consisting

607
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:59,000
of two separate loops is just the product

608
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,000
of the Feynman diagrams for each loop

609
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,000
separately.

610
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:05,000
If there's a plus sign

611
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:07,000
for one loop,

612
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:09,000
then there will be a plus sign for two loops.

613
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,000
What about if there's a minus sign

614
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:13,000
for one loop?

615
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,000
There'll still be a plus sign for two loops.

616
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,000
So the answer for two loops

617
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,000
like this, disconnected loops

618
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:21,000
like this, is always positive.

619
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,000
Whether or not

620
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,000
the sign for one loop is negative.

621
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,000
Now, let's

622
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,000
do the following.

623
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,000
Let's assume

624
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:33,000
that our particles are fermions.

625
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:35,000
Let's break this over here

626
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,000
and look at it

627
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,000
right in the middle

628
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,000
at t equals zero.

629
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,000
While these two things are here,

630
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,000
let's put them

631
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,000
close enough together

632
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,000
that they almost overlap.

633
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:55,000
What happens

634
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,000
What happens

635
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,000
to the amplitude

636
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:01,000
for a system

637
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,000
if you interchange

638
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:05,000
two bosons?

639
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:07,000
If you take the two bosons

640
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:09,000
and exchange them?

641
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:11,000
Plus sign.

642
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:13,000
The wave function for bosons

643
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:15,000
is always symmetric,

644
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:17,000
which means if you interchange them,

645
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:19,000
plus sign.

646
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,000
What happens if you take two fermions

647
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,000
and interchange them?

648
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:25,000
Minus sign.

649
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,000
That's the property of fermions and bosons.

650
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,000
For fermions, the wave functions are anti-symmetric,

651
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,000
and so if you interchange the two fermions,

652
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:33,000
you get a minus sign.

653
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:35,000
For bosons, it's a plus sign.

654
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,000
So, we can compare two things.

655
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:39,000
And the first thing,

656
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:41,000
we take these and we don't interchange them.

657
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:43,000
That's just two loops.

658
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:45,000
And the second thing,

659
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:49,000
before closing it up,

660
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,000
we interchange them.

661
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,000
We just interchange which one is which.

662
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,000
We just interchange which one is which.

663
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,000
What happens

664
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,000
if they're fermions?

665
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,000
If they're fermions, we get a minus sign.

666
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,000
If they're bosons,

667
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,000
we get a plus sign from here.

668
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:07,000
We've managed

669
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:09,000
to go from two loops

670
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:11,000
to one loop,

671
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:13,000
this is one loop now.

672
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,000
This is just one loop.

673
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,000
It's one loop.

674
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:19,000
We went from two loops

675
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:21,000
to one loop just by

676
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:23,000
interchanging two particles.

677
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:25,000
Two loops necessarily

678
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:27,000
has a plus sign.

679
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,000
If the loops involve

680
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:31,000
fermions,

681
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:33,000
then there's a sign change

682
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,000
when we interchange the two particles.

683
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,000
So a single loop like this

684
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:39,000
for fermions necessarily has

685
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:41,000
a minus sign associated with it.

686
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:43,000
A single loop for bosons

687
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,000
has a plus sign

688
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:47,000
in the amplitude.

689
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:49,000
The consequences of this are profound.

690
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:51,000
What it says is that

691
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:53,000
the contribution

692
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:55,000
to the vacuum energy

693
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,000
of a loop

694
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:59,000
of fermions

695
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:01,000
is negative.

696
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,000
The contribution of a loop of bosons

697
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,000
is positive.

698
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:07,000
That's very interesting.

699
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,000
We have this very strange

700
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:11,000
puzzle about the vacuum energy

701
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:13,000
that we talked about last time.

702
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:15,000
The vacuum energy, whatever it is

703
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,000
in nature, is very, very small.

704
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,000
We call it dark energy.

705
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,000
It's extremely small.

706
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,000
The amount of it in this room

707
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:25,000
is extremely negligible.

708
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,000
And

709
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:29,000
the naive calculation

710
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,000
in quantum field theory

711
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:33,000
would give an answer 123 orders

712
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:35,000
of magnitude larger.

713
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:37,000
It is at least

714
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,000
at minimum interesting

715
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:41,000
that the quantum field theory answer

716
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:43,000
can either be positive or negative

717
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:45,000
and that it's negative for fermions

718
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:47,000
and positive for bosons.

719
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:51,000
The answer depends on all kinds of details

720
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:53,000
about the particle. It depends on the mass

721
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:55,000
of the particle and other things.

722
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,000
It depends on its charge. It

723
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:57,000
depends on all sorts of things.

724
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:59,000
But at least we've encountered

725
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:01,000
a way to be able

726
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,000
to get both plus signs and minus signs.

727
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:05,000
The fact that they cancel out

728
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:07,000
